episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: Clueless Dunder Mifflin manager Michael Scott welcomes a documentary crew to observe the office just as he learns that his branch could be downsized.

episodes.title: Diversity Day
episodes.description: After receiving complaints about an employee's unsolicited repeat performance of a risqu√© comedy routine, Michael leads a diversity training session.

episodes.title: Health Care
episodes.description: The company is cutting back on health care, which means switching to a plan with fewer benefits. Michael sends Dwight to tell the employees.

episodes.title: The Alliance
episodes.description: With rumors of downsizing floating around the office, a nervous Dwight approaches Jim about forming an alliance to protect their jobs.

episodes.title: Basketball
episodes.description: After planning a basketball game between the office and warehouse workers, Michael picks his "dream team" -- led by the company's sole black employee.

episodes.title: Hot Girl
episodes.description: When an attractive woman shows up on the premises to sell handbags, Michael sees an opportunity for a red-hot office romance.

episodes.title: The Dundies
episodes.description: When corporate won't pay for the annual employee appreciation awards ceremony, Michael is forced to create a memorable evening on a shoestring budget.

episodes.title: Sexual Harassment
episodes.description: When HR announces a crackdown on sexual harassment, Michael is forced to curb his habit of forwarding inappropriate e-mails to his underlings.

episodes.title: Office Olympics
episodes.description: With Michael and Dwight out of the office on a "work-related" condo search, Jim and Pam hold the first Dunder-Mifflin Olympic Games.

episodes.title: The Fire
episodes.description: To pass the time during an unplanned fire drill, Jim organizes games of "Desert Island," "Would You Rather..." and "Who Would You Do?"

episodes.title: Halloween
episodes.description: As he watches his employees prepare for the office's annual Halloween party, Michael agonizes over which of them he'll fire.

episodes.title: The Fight
episodes.description: When Dwight, who holds a purple belt in karate, knocks out Michael during a playful scuffle, his humiliated boss invites everyone to a rematch.

episodes.title: The Client
episodes.description: Declaring Chili's "the new golf course," Michael convinces Jan that it's a great place to woo an important client.

episodes.title: Performance Review
episodes.description: Instead of talking to his employees about their work, Michael uses their annual review time to gather feedback on his "relationship" with Jan.

episodes.title: Email Surveillance
episodes.description: While monitoring his employees' e-mails, Michael stumbles upon an invitation to a barbecue at Jim's apartment that Michael was not invited to.

episodes.title: Christmas Party
episodes.description: Flush with cash from a recent bonus, Michael throws an office Christmas party. Jim begins planning the perfect Secret Santa gift for Pam.

episodes.title: Booze Cruise
episodes.description: The staff sets sail on a "booze cruise" that was chartered by Michael to boost office morale and kick-start a day of leadership training.

episodes.title: The Injury
episodes.description: In an unprecedented breakfast-in-bed accident, Michael burns his foot on a George Foreman Grill and demands that his staff caters to his every whim.

episodes.title: The Secret
episodes.description: Frantic that a tactless Michael will reveal his secret crush on Pam, Jim tries desperately to bond with him over an uncomfortable lunch at Hooters.

episodes.title: The Carpet
episodes.description: A stench in Michael's office leads to a game of musical chairs, prompting Michael to take over Jim's cubicle and reminisce about his past.

episodes.title: Boys and Girls
episodes.description: When Jan holds a "Women in the Workplace" seminar for the female employees, a jealous Michael retaliates by gathering the men for their own meeting.

episodes.title: Valentine's Day
episodes.description: Michael and Jan head to New York City for a corporate meeting on Valentine's Day, prompting rumors that they're actually an item.

episodes.title: Dwight's Speech
episodes.description: After being named Salesman of the Year, Dwight must confront his fear of public speaking. Pam announces that she and Roy have set a wedding date.

episodes.title: Take Your Daughter to Work Day
episodes.description: "Take Your Daughter to Work Day" sets the stage for a series of classic Michael gaffes.

episodes.title: Michael's Birthday
episodes.description: Determined to enjoy his birthday despite everyone's anxiety over whether Kevin has skin cancer, Michael takes the entire crew to an ice-skating rink.

episodes.title: Drug Testing
episodes.description: After finding a half-smoked joint, Dwight launches an investigation to find the culprit and earns the honorary title of official security supervisor.

episodes.title: Conflict Resolution
episodes.description: When Michael takes over Toby's conflict-resolution duties, his approach of encouraging "cooperation through confrontation" may ruin office morale.

episodes.title: Casino Night
episodes.description: Michael finds himself trapped in an awkward love triangle when his boss, Jan, and his realtor, Carole, both accept his invitation to casino night.

episodes.title: Gay Witch Hunt
episodes.description: Jim tries to adjust to his promotion and life away from Pam. Back in Scranton, Michael teams with Dwight to identify the homosexuals in the office.

episodes.title: The Convention
episodes.description: At a convention, Michael and Dwight connect with Jim for a crazy party in their hotel room. Pam prepares for her first date since her breakup.

episodes.title: The Coup
episodes.description: Jan arrives during Michael's "Movie Monday" and is mad that nobody is working. Dwight secretly meets with Jan about taking over Michael's job.

episodes.title: Grief Counseling
episodes.description: Michael looks for a way to properly honor his former mentor, while Jim's co-workers start to resent him when the boss gives him more responsibilities.

episodes.title: Initiation
episodes.description: Dwight gives Ryan a lesson in salesmanship and takes him to the family beet farm. Michael and Stanley eagerly anticipate their free yummy treats.

episodes.title: Diwali
episodes.description: When Kelly invites the staff to attend a Hindu festival, Michael takes the opportunity to bring everyone closer and later makes a big announcement.

episodes.title: Branch Closing
episodes.description: The mood in the office takes a depressing turn when Jan informs Michael that Dunder Mifflin's board plans to close the Scranton branch.

episodes.title: The Merger
episodes.description: With Stamford's employees joining the Scranton team -- reuniting Pam and Jim -- Michael tries to impress everyone with a special welcome video.

episodes.title: The Convict
episodes.description: Michael suspects one of the new Stamford transfers is an ex-con. Andy turns to Jim for advice about how to win Pam over.

episodes.title: A Benihana Christmas
episodes.description: Michael makes a special Christmas greeting card for Carol. Meanwhile, Angela, Pam and Karen don't see eye to eye about the annual yuletide party.

episodes.title: Back from Vacation
episodes.description: When Karen moves next door to Jim, the two have their first major argument. Michael lets a big secret slip while showing pictures of his Jamaica trip.

episodes.title: Traveling Salesmen
episodes.description: Jim and Dwight are forced to team up when Michael sends the staff out on sales calls. Later, Michael chooses Andy as his partner.

episodes.title: The Return
episodes.description: Andy maneuvers to be Michael's second in command and irritates everyone, especially Jim. The party-planning committee prepares for Oscar's return.

episodes.title: Ben Franklin
episodes.description: Michael hires adult entertainers to spice up Phyllis' wedding shower. Meanwhile, Karen asks Pam whether she still has feelings for Jim.

episodes.title: Phyllis's Wedding
episodes.description: Michael is honored when given the task of pushing Phyllis' dad down the aisle at her wedding. Dwight wants to ensure that no one crashes the ceremony.

episodes.title: Business School
episodes.description: While Pam enters an art exhibition, Ryan brings Michael to his business class as a guest speaker. Back at the office, Dwight tries to capture a bat.

episodes.title: Cocktails
episodes.description: During a party at the chief financial officer's home, Michael spills the beans about his relationship with Jan. And Pam gets assertive with Roy.

episodes.title: The Negotiation
episodes.description: An angry Roy storms into the office looking to hurt Jim, but an unexpected hero stops him. Darryl and Michael negotiate Darryl's pay raise.

episodes.title: Safety Training
episodes.description: During safety-training day, Michael is determined to show everyone that safety is no joke, and Dwight helps him prepare an over-the-top demonstration.

episodes.title: Product Recall
episodes.description: Paper with an obscene watermark is inadvertently sent out, sending Michael into damage-control mode and forcing Angela to deal with angry callers.

episodes.title: Women's Appreciation
episodes.description: When Phyllis gets flashed, Michael organizes a special outing for the ladies to boost their morale as Andy and Dwight try to track down the culprit.

episodes.title: Beach Games
episodes.description: Michael takes the staff for a day of fun at Lake Scranton, but the fun stops when he divides everyone into tribes and forces them to compete in challenges.

episodes.title: The Job
episodes.description: Karen and Jim interview for an opening at the corporate offices, though Michael thinks he has the job sewn up. Jan wants another chance with Michael.

episodes.title: Fun Run
episodes.description: A freak accident spurs Michael to organize an employee charity run. Jim and Pam go public with their love. Dwight destroys Angela's personal property.

episodes.title: Dunder Mifflin Infinity
episodes.description: Newly promoted Ryan returns to the Scranton branch and receives a cold reception to his announcement of the company's new website.

episodes.title: Launch Party
episodes.description: Dwight tries to beat the company's new website in one-day sales. Michael retaliates when he isn't invited to the site launch party in New York.

episodes.title: Money
episodes.description: Jan's excessive spending causes major money problems for Michael. Jim and Pam spend an unforgettable night on Dwight's farm.

episodes.title: Local Ad
episodes.description: Michael writes, produces and directs a commercial promoting the Scranton branch. Brokenhearted Dwight learns an intriguing secret about Angela.

episodes.title: Branch Wars
episodes.description: Furious when Karen offers Stanley a position at her office branch in Utica, Michael tricks Jim into joining him and Dwight in a prank against her.

episodes.title: Survivor Man
episodes.description: When Michael is excluded from an executive retreat in the woods, he treats himself to a lone "Survivor Man" style campout.

episodes.title: The Deposition
episodes.description: Jan tries to manipulate Michael in a bogus lawsuit against Dunder Mifflin. Pam is incensed when Kelly gloats over an incident between Jim and Darryl.

episodes.title: Dinner Party
episodes.description: The employees witness Michael's dysfunctional relationship with Jan at a dinner party, and Dwight tries to make Angela jealous with an unusual date.

episodes.title: The Chair Model
episodes.description: Dunder Mifflin loses two assigned parking spaces, and Michael's infatuation with a catalog model makes him reconsider his relationship with Jan.

episodes.title: Night Out
episodes.description: Michael and Dwight go clubbing with Ryan. Back at the office, Jim's plan to save the staff from a Saturday at the office backfires.

episodes.title: Did I Stutter
episodes.description: Stanley disrespects Michael in front of the other employees, and a used-car purchase between Dwight and Andy creates a major rift.

episodes.title: Job Fair
episodes.description: Michael, Pam, Oscar and Darryl attend a job fair at Pam's alma mater. Across town, Jim attempts his first "hard sell" over a round of golf.

episodes.title: Goodbye, Toby
episodes.description: On Toby's last day at the company, Michael falls in love with his replacement. Jim's elaborate plans for his proposal to Pam are derailed.

episodes.title: Weight Loss: Part 1
episodes.description: A company weight loss initiative has everyone obsessed with their diet. Michael pursues a friendship with his new HR rep and Jim pops the question.

episodes.title: Weight Loss: Part 2
episodes.description: The office continues its efforts to win the Dunder Mifflin weight loss initiative. Meanwhile, Jim misses Pam, who's attending art school in New York.

episodes.title: Business Ethics
episodes.description: Holly's business ethics seminar gets out of control when Michael lets everyone speak freely about their unethical behavior at work.

episodes.title: Baby Shower
episodes.description: Michael prepares for Jan's baby by having Dwight go over various birthing scenarios, and tells Holly he'll pretend to dislike her for Jan's benefit.

episodes.title: Crime Aid
episodes.description: Michael and Holly get an early start on their date night. When the office is robbed, Michael holds an auction to raise money for items lost.

episodes.title: Employee Transfer
episodes.description: Pam is the only one wearing a costume on Halloween. Holly and Michael take the long trip to Nashua after they get some shocking news from corporate.

episodes.title: Customer Survey
episodes.description: Dwight and Jim are shocked by the results of the annual customer survey report. Pam and Jim spend every minute together via Bluetooth.

episodes.title: Business Trip
episodes.description: Michael is ecstatic when he's sent on a business trip. Andy and Oscar become unlikely friends when Michael decides to bring them along.

episodes.title: Frame Toby
episodes.description: Someone makes a huge mess in the microwave and will not clean it up. Michael realizes that changes in his staff have occurred without his knowing.

episodes.title: The Surplus
episodes.description: Michael learns that the office must spend a $4300 surplus or lose it, and chaos breaks out as everyone fights to get what they want.

episodes.title: Moroccan Christmas
episodes.description: Phyllis's party goes up in flames when Meredith's hair catches on fire, and Dwight corners the market on the hottest toy of the Christmas season.

episodes.title: The Duel
episodes.description: Andy still doesn't know about Angela's affair with Dwight. When Michael spills the beans, Dwight and Andy take matters into their own hands.

episodes.title: Prince Family Paper
episodes.description: Michael and Dwight go undercover to spy on a rival paper company. Meanwhile, the rest of the office debates a burning question: Is Hilary Swank hot?

episodes.title: Stress Relief: Part 1
episodes.description: Dwight's fire drill causes Stanley to collapse from a heart attack. Afterward, Dwight must try to make amends to the stressed-out office.

episodes.title: Stress Relief: Part 2
episodes.description: When Michael learns that his frazzled employees consider him their number one stressor at work, he insists on a no-holds-barred roast of himself.

episodes.title: Lecture Circuit: Part 1
episodes.description: Michael visits other branches to explain Scranton's relative success. Dwight and Jim, heading the party-planning committee, forget a birthday.

episodes.title: Lecture Circuit: Part 2
episodes.description: Michael and Pam continue their tour of the branches. Dwight and Jim struggle with their party-planning duties. Angela's new cat causes a stir.

episodes.title: Blood Drive
episodes.description: On Valentine's Day, Michael meets a mysterious woman, Dwight and Kevin find single women, and Jim and Pam are banished for public affection.

episodes.title: Golden Ticket
episodes.description: Michael causes a huge problem when he comes up with the idea to put "golden tickets" into packages of paper for clients to redeem for discounts.

episodes.title: New Boss
episodes.description: Michael has big plans for his 15th anniversary party, but the company's new, no-nonsense vice president has some ideas of his own.

episodes.title: Two Weeks
episodes.description: Michael's relationship with the new vice president becomes increasingly tense, Pam battles a new copier and Kelly develops a crush.

episodes.title: Dream Team
episodes.description: After making a bad impression on his new boss, Jim runs into him during a parking lot soccer game. Meanwhile, Michael is afraid to leave his house.

episodes.title: Michael Scott Paper Company
episodes.description: Dwight and Andy plan a hunting trip. Asked for a "rundown," Jim spends his day figuring out what that is. Michael hosts a Paper & Pancakes lunch.

episodes.title: Heavy Competition
episodes.description: Dwight's loyalty to Michael is tested when he finds a new hero in Charles. Meanwhile, Andy tries to provide for all of Jim's emotional needs.

episodes.title: Broke
episodes.description: Michael's new company struggles to make early-morning deliveries, while the office tries to get their expense reports in on time.

episodes.title: Casual Friday
episodes.description: Michael mediates a dispute within his new sales team. Meanwhile, trouble brews among several employees over the term "Casual Fridays."

episodes.title: Cafe Disco
episodes.description: Michael gets into the caf√©/disco scene. Meanwhile, Pam and Jim decide to take a secret trip.

episodes.title: Company Picnic
episodes.description: Michael and Holly are reunited at the annual company picnic, where the office also competes in the picnic's volleyball tournament.

episodes.title: Gossip
episodes.description: Michael feels left out as the rest of the office gossips about the summer interns. Meanwhile, Andy struggles with heterosexuality.

episodes.title: The Meeting
episodes.description: A request by Jim leaves Michael feeling insecure and defensive. Meanwhile, Pam deals with the guest list for the wedding.

episodes.title: The Promotion
episodes.description: David Wallace breaks the bad news that not everyone will get a raise this year, and Dwight reaches his breaking point with Jim.

episodes.title: Niagara: Part 1
episodes.description: In part 1 of a 2-part episode, the office travels to Niagara Falls to celebrate Jim and Pam's wedding under orders not to mention Pam's pregnancy.

episodes.title: Niagara: Part 2
episodes.description: In part 2 of a 2-part episode, Michael, Dwight and Andy all want to hook up with guests at Jim and Pam's wedding, and Michael and Dwight meet twins.

episodes.title: Mafia
episodes.description: Michael meets with an insurance salesman in the office, but Dwight and Andy think he's part of the mafia. Erin accidentally ruins Pam's painting.

episodes.title: The Lover
episodes.description: Michael shocks Jim and Pam when he reveals the identity of the new woman he's been dating. Dwight apologizes to Jim with a strange peace offering.

episodes.title: Koi Pond
episodes.description: Michael gets teased by everyone at the office after he takes an embarrassing fall at a meeting. Pam and Andy go on a sales call together.

episodes.title: Double Date
episodes.description: Jim and Pam have no choice but to go out with Michael and Helene. Strangely, Dwight is doing nice things for everyone in the office.

episodes.title: Murder
episodes.description: Michael forces the office into a day of strange diversions, upsetting Jim and leading others to wonder if Michael has gone insane.

episodes.title: Shareholder Meeting
episodes.description: Michael gets excited when he's invited by David Wallace to be honored onstage at the Dunder Mifflin shareholder meeting in New York.

episodes.title: Scott's Tots
episodes.description: Michael can't keep a promise he made to a group of kids 10 years ago. Meanwhile, Jim starts an Employee of the Month program to improve morale.

episodes.title: Secret Santa
episodes.description: Michael is outraged when Jim allows Phyllis to be Santa at the office Christmas party. Jim and Dwight try to get everyone into the holiday spirit.

episodes.title: The Banker
episodes.description: When a potential buyer visits, Michael, Dwight, Andy and Pam pull out all the stops in hopes of impressing him with their high-profile contacts.

episodes.title: Sabre
episodes.description: Michael struggles to accept Sabre's new policies; Pam and Jim interview with a prestigious daycare; Andy and Erin work on a welcome song for Sabre.

episodes.title: Manager and the Salesman
episodes.description: The office loves Sabre CEO Jo Bennett, until she says that there can't be two branch managers and that either Michael or Jim must go back to sales.

episodes.title: Delivery: Part 1
episodes.description: Pam's contractions begin, and the rest of the office tries to distract her from the pain with food and entertainment.

episodes.title: Delivery: Part 2
episodes.description: Everybody plays the waiting game as Pam prepares to give birth. Dwight decides to fix the cabinets in Pam and Jim's kitchen.

episodes.title: St. Patrick's Day
episodes.description: Michael mistakenly believes that he impressed Jo; Dwight disrupts Jim's first day back from paternity leave; Andy and Erin have an unusual first date.

episodes.title: New Leads
episodes.description: When the sales staff lets Sabre's new "sales is king" policy get to their heads, Michael hides their new, prized leads.

episodes.title: Happy Hour
episodes.description: Michael gets kicked out of the bar when he tries to impress a friend of Jim and Pam's. Andy and Erin try to keep their relationships under wraps.

episodes.title: Secretary's Day
episodes.description: Andy pulls out all the stops for Erin on Secretary's Day, but when Michael takes her to lunch, he lets slip about Andy's relationship with Angela.

episodes.title: Body Language
episodes.description: Pam and Jim work on their first sales pitch to a local restaurant, while Dwight encourages Kelly to try out for the minority training program.

episodes.title: The Cover-Up
episodes.description: Michael has Dwight investigate when he suspects Donna is cheating. Meanwhile, Andy is frustrated when no one takes his customer's complaint seriously.

episodes.title: The Chump
episodes.description: Michael is oddly upbeat after hearing bad news about Donna; new parents Pam and Jim can't stay awake; Dwight won't honor his contract with Angela.

episodes.title: Whistleblower
episodes.description: When the press reports that Sabre's printers catch on fire, Jo hunts for the whistleblower. Everyone suspects Andy, who denies leaking the story.

episodes.title: Nepotism
episodes.description: Michael refuses to fire the office assistant, and Andy plays it cool after Erin shows interest in another man. Meanwhile, Pam plays an office prank.

episodes.title: Counseling
episodes.description: Michael goes to Toby for counseling, and Dwight vows revenge after a shop owner snubs him. Meanwhile, Pam conspires to change her job title.

episodes.title: Andy's Play
episodes.description: Andy invites the entire office to his community theater production of "Sweeney Todd," while Jim and Pam struggle with their incompetent babysitter.

episodes.title: Sex Ed
episodes.description: Michael, believing he has herpes, contacts all his ex-girlfriends. Andy tries to play on Erin's compassionate side by holding a sex education meeting.

episodes.title: The Sting
episodes.description: When a competing sales associate steals a Dunder Mifflin client, Michael, Jim and Dwight set up a sting to find out his secrets. Andy starts a band.

episodes.title: Costume Contest
episodes.description: When Darryl takes an idea to corporate over his head, Michael freaks out. Everyone gets competitive as the Halloween costume contest gets underway.

episodes.title: Christening
episodes.description: Michael invites the entire office to celebrate the christening of Pam and Jim's baby, Cece.

episodes.title: Viewing Party
episodes.description: Erin and Gabe invite the office over for a "Glee" viewing party. Michael deals poorly with people calling Gabe his boss. Andy grows jealous of Gabe.

episodes.title: WUPHF.com
episodes.description: More than money is at stake as Michael helps charm people into investing in Ryan's start-up. Dwight creates a hay festival in the parking lot.

episodes.title: China
episodes.description: After reading about China growing as a global power, Michael decides China must be stopped before it takes over the United States.

episodes.title: Classy Christmas: Part 1
episodes.description: Toby has to take a leave of absence and corporate sends Holly Flax to cover for him. Michael forces Pam to throw a second Christmas party.

episodes.title: Classy Christmas: Part 2
episodes.description: Michael wants to throw a second Christmas party to celebrate Holly's returns to Scranton. Jim regrets agreeing to a snowball fight with Dwight.

episodes.title: Ultimatum
episodes.description: Michael prepares himself for the good or bad news about Holly and her boyfriend. Pam puts up a board for everyone to post New Year's resolutions.

episodes.title: The Seminar
episodes.description: Dealing with low sales, Andy holds a business seminar with the help of some special guests. Michael and Holly turn the event into an improv challenge.

episodes.title: The Search
episodes.description: When Jim gets an emergency call from Helene, he leaves Michael in the bathroom of a gas station. Holly, Erin and Dwight set out to find Michael.

episodes.title: PDA
episodes.description: It's Valentine's Day, and Michael and Holly's displays of affection are making everyone uncomfortable. A champagne lunch causes complications.

episodes.title: Threat Level Midnight
episodes.description: After 11 years in the making, Michael is finally ready to present his movie, "Threat Level Midnight," to his co-workers and love interest, Holly.

episodes.title: Todd Packer
episodes.description: After many years and motel rooms, traveling salesman (and Michael's best friend) Todd is ready to leave the road and take a desk job in the office.

episodes.title: Garage Sale
episodes.description: The warehouse and office staff hold a garage sale; Michael seeks his coworkers' advice on an important decision.

episodes.title: Training Day
episodes.description: Everyone hopes to make a good first impression on the new manager: Andy finds himself typecast, while Jim and Pam worry they've come on too strong.

episodes.title: Michael's Last Dundies
episodes.description: Michael trains Deangeleo to take over the job of hosting the Dundie Awards. Erin struggles with her dislike of her boyfriend, Gabe.

episodes.title: Goodbye, Michael
episodes.description: Michael, about to leave for Colorado, says his goodbyes to each co-worker. Deangelo and Andy scramble to keep Michael's biggest clients.

episodes.title: The Inner Circle
episodes.description: Deangelo's true management style is finally revealed.

episodes.title: Dwight K. Schrute, (Acting) Manager
episodes.description: Dwight takes over as acting manager and applies Draconian tactics to the office. Meanwhile, Gabe tries to win Erin back.

episodes.title: Search Committee: Part 1
episodes.description: Jim heads a search committee that interviews the managerial candidates, including Andy and Darryl. Dwight tries to get back in the race.

episodes.title: Search Committee: Part 2
episodes.description: Jim heads a search committee that interviews the managerial candidates, including Andy and Darryl. Dwight tries to get back in the race.

episodes.title: The List
episodes.description: The staff is hit with a double whammy as Scranton gets a new regional manager and Robert California takes the helm of Dunder Mifflin Sabre as CEO.

episodes.title: The Incentive
episodes.description: Robert California wants to double sales growth, and Andy responds with an unusual incentive plan to motivate the team.

episodes.title: Lotto
episodes.description: When the warehouse crew quits after winning the lotto, the team pitches in to keep Dunder Mifflin humming.

episodes.title: Garden Party
episodes.description: Trying to gain some respect from his family and new boss, Andy throws a garden party at Schrute Farms.

episodes.title: Spooked
episodes.description: Erin struggles to pull off the ultimate Halloween party, juggling the expectations of Robert California, Andy and the staff.

episodes.title: Doomsday
episodes.description: Challenged to improve productivity, Dwight develops an accountability booster program that threatens to get the entire office fired.

episodes.title: Pam's Replacement
episodes.description: Pam's convinced her temp replacement is the apple of Jim's eye; Robert California has a musical proposition for Andy, Darryl and Kevin.

episodes.title: Gettysburg
episodes.description: Andy tries to fire up the team with a trip to Gettysburg; Robert California challenges the team to think way outside the box.

episodes.title: Mrs. California
episodes.description: Andy's in a tough spot when Robert California sends him mixed messages about hiring his wife.

episodes.title: Christmas Wishes
episodes.description: Andy wants to make everyone's Christmas wishes come true -- no matter how distraught they are.

episodes.title: Trivia
episodes.description: Pressed to boost the bottom line, Andy finds a novel way to improve sales, while Dwight explores corporate opportunities outside Scranton.

episodes.title: Pool Party
episodes.description: Robert invites the staff to his house for one last party before the home goes up for sale.

episodes.title: Jury Duty
episodes.description: Jim comes under fire when the office realizes he skipped work by faking jury duty to spend time with Pam and the new baby.

episodes.title: Special Project
episodes.description: Dwight is recruited to lead a team headed to Florida to create a chain of Sabre retail stores.

episodes.title: Tallahassee
episodes.description: To get noticed by Corporate, Dwight takes his team to Tallahassee to conceive a new chain of Sabre retail stores.

episodes.title: After Hours
episodes.description: Nellie pits Packer against Dwight for the VP job, Jim fends off an amorous intruder, and Andy works the Scranton team overtime.

episodes.title: Test the Store
episodes.description: Dwight plans an impressive presentation for the Sabre store, and Andy suffers an embarrassing injury.

episodes.title: Last Day in Florida
episodes.description: Robert hates Nellie's business plan, and Jim tries to save Dwight from being fired. Meanwhile, Andy learns that Erin isn't returning to Scranton.

episodes.title: Get the Girl
episodes.description: As Andy heads south to Florida to sweep Erin off her feet, Nellie makes herself at home in his office in Scranton.

episodes.title: Welcome Party
episodes.description: As Erin and Andy plot how he should break up with Jessica, Robert California orders the office to throw a welcome party for Nellie.

episodes.title: Angry Andy
episodes.description: Andy's job -- and manhood -- are called into question as he returns with Erin to Scranton.

episodes.title: Fundraiser
episodes.description: Unemployed Andy crashes a fundraiser for the Senator -- and ends up the unlikely owner of a dozen disabled dogs.

episodes.title: Turf War
episodes.description: A drunken Robert California closes a branch, igniting a sales war.

episodes.title: Free Family Portrait Studio
episodes.description: Dwight raises suspicions by offering free portraits; Andy returns with some self-satisfying news.

episodes.title: New Guys
episodes.description: Jim and Dwight are thrown off by the arrival of two young employees that the others dub "the new Jim" and "Dwight Jr." Andy returns from training.

episodes.title: Roy's Wedding
episodes.description: Pam and Jim go to Roy's wedding, where his toast takes everyone by surprise -- causing Pam and Jim to examine their own relationship.

episodes.title: Andy's Ancestry
episodes.description: Andy learns he is related to Michelle Obama, causing a stir around the office. Jim's elaborate trick has Dwight thinking Jim is an Asian man.

episodes.title: Work Bus
episodes.description: After Jim convinces Dwight that the building is unsafe, Dwight rents a bus and sets up the office inside -- and eventually they hit the road.

episodes.title: Here Comes Treble
episodes.description: It's Halloween in the office, and Andy invites his college a cappella group to perform, which leads to a confrontation with his frenemy Broccoli Rob.

episodes.title: The Boat
episodes.description: Andy must man up when his dad blows all of the family's money. When Dwight is interviewed on local radio, Jim tortures him with bizarre call-ins.

episodes.title: The Whale
episodes.description: To help Dwight overcome his greatest professional handicap -- selling to women -- Pam and the ladies teach him how to interact with female clients.

episodes.title: The Target
episodes.description: Angela discovers her husband's affair and goes to Dwight for help. Jim needs a favor from Stanley and Phyllis, who milk it for all it's worth.

episodes.title: Dwight Christmas
episodes.description: When the party planning committee drops the ball on the Christmas party, Dwight gets everyone to celebrate a traditional Schrute German Christmas.

episodes.title: Lice
episodes.description: Pam accidentally brings lice into the office and lets Meredith take the fall. Meanwhile, Jim woos a potential business associate in Philadelphia.

episodes.title: Suit Warehouse
episodes.description: Dwight and Clark pose as father and son to make a sale. Meanwhile, Darryl interviews at Jim's company and Pam comes for a surprise visit.

episodes.title: Customer Loyalty
episodes.description: Dwight tries to prevent Darryl's move to Athlead. Jim is forced to miss Cece's first recital when a big investor exits his new company.

episodes.title: Junior Salesman
episodes.description: David Wallace tasks Dwight with finding a new part-time salesman to fill in for Jim. Dwight assembles a super-team of his cronies, starting with Mose.

episodes.title: Vandalism
episodes.description: When Pam's warehouse mural is defaced, Dwight and Nellie spring to action. Darryl has difficulty dealing with Jim's habits in their shared apartment.

episodes.title: Couple's Discount
episodes.description: The office pairs off into pretend couples to take advantage of a Valentine's Day discount at the mall. Erin assures Pete she will break up with Andy.

episodes.title: Moving On
episodes.description: Pam interviews for a job in Philadelphia with a manager who gives her deja-vu. Dwight brings Angela on a mission to clean his elderly Aunt Shirley.

episodes.title: The Farm
episodes.description: Dwight travels home for a customary Schrute funeral. He and his siblings receive a surprise inheritance that's not entirely welcome.

episodes.title: Promos
episodes.description: Everyone is excited when promos start running on TV for the documentary. Dwight makes Angela jealous when he starts dating a Brussels sprout farmer.

episodes.title: Stairmageddon
episodes.description: "Stairmaggedon" strikes when the elevator goes out and everyone is forced to take the stairs. Dwight forces Stanley to do an important sales call.

episodes.title: Paper Airplane
episodes.description: Dwight and Angela compete in an office-wide paper airplane contest. A local talent agent helps Andy with his first acting role in an industrial film.

episodes.title: Livin' the Dream
episodes.description: Andy tries to work up the nerve to quit his job and pursue his dreams of stardom. Dwight finally receives his karate black belt from his new sensei.

episodes.title: A.A.R.M
episodes.description: While the office readies for the documentary premiere, Jim holds tryouts to hire an assistant to the assistant to the regional manager.

episodes.title: Finale
episodes.description: In the series finale, months after the airing of the documentary, the workers of Dunder Mifflin, past and present, gather for a wedding.

episodes.title: Extreme Aggressor
episodes.description: When a fourth woman goes missing in Seattle during the course of four months, the team is brought in to profile her captor.

episodes.title: Compulsion
episodes.description: When a college campus is terrorized by a serial arsonist, the team attempts to identify the firestarter before he strikes again.

episodes.title: Won't Get Fooled Again
episodes.description: Gideon and his team track down a copycat bomber terrorizing a quiet community.

episodes.title: Plain Sight
episodes.description: Gideon and his team must profile a serial rapist and murderer who preys on women in affluent neighborhoods.

episodes.title: Broken Mirror
episodes.description: The behavioral analysis unit is called in when the daughter of a U.S. district attorney is kidnapped.

episodes.title: L.D.S.K.
episodes.description: The FBI profilers must track down a sniper who is preying on victims in the middle of the day.

episodes.title: The Fox
episodes.description: The behavioral analysis unit tracks a serial killer who takes families hostage before they leave for vacation.

episodes.title: Natural Born Killer
episodes.description: The FBI profilers suspect a serial killer is involved in the disappearance of an undercover cop.

episodes.title: Derailed
episodes.description: Elle is caught in the crossfire when she and several other passengers are taken hostage on board a train.

episodes.title: The Popular Kids
episodes.description: Gideon and Hotchner investigate whether or not a cult is responsible for the murder of two high school students in a small town.

episodes.title: Blood Hungry
episodes.description: Gideon and Hotchner attempt to identify a killer whose delusional fantasies lead him to commit murder.

episodes.title: What Fresh Hell?
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team investigate the kidnapping of a young girl from a seemingly safe neighborhood playground.

episodes.title: Poison
episodes.description: The FBI profilers investigate a mass poisoning in a small town in order to determine what the common denominator is among the victims.

episodes.title: Riding the Lightning
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team interview husband and wife serial killers awaiting execution on death row.

episodes.title: Unfinished Business
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team attempt to capture a serial killer who has resurfaced after 20 years of silence.

episodes.title: The Tribe
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team examine the circumstances surrounding the mass murder of five college students killed in an empty house.

episodes.title: A REal Rain
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team investigate a series of murders that appear to be the work of a vigilante seeking justice for previous crime victims.

episodes.title: Somebody's Watching
episodes.description: Gideon and Dr. Reid investigate the case of a Hollywood starlet whose stalker turns into a killer.

episodes.title: Machismo
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team head to Mexico to aid in the investigation of a serial killer who preys on the elderly, on CRIMINAL MINDS.

episodes.title: Charm and Harm
episodes.description: A quick change artist on a killing spree takes Gideon, Hotchner and their team on a wild chase throughout the south.

episodes.title: Secrets and Lies
episodes.description: The behavioral analysis unit faces one of their toughest challenges yet when they must help identify a double agent working within the CIA.

episodes.title: The Fisher King: Part 1
episodes.description: While on a rare vacation from work, the members of the behavioral analysis team are each sent a highly personal clue that ensnarls them in a mystery.

episodes.title: The Fisher King: Part 2
episodes.description: Gideon and the team continue to search for the psychopath who used personal information to ensnarl them in the mystery of a missing young girl.

episodes.title: P911
episodes.description: A former profiler turns to Gideon and his team for help saving a young boy who has turned up in an online auction after disappearing for a year.

episodes.title: The Perfect Storm
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team investigate a series of murders that may have been committed by a pair of suspects working together.

episodes.title: Psychodrama
episodes.description: The behavioral analysis team investigates a series of bizarre bank robberies in which the robber makes the victims disrobe.

episodes.title: Aftermath
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team profile a serial rapist who has changed tactics in order to continue his crime spree.

episodes.title: The Boogeyman
episodes.description: The Behavioral Analysis Unit investigates the mysterious deaths of several children in a small town.

episodes.title: North Mammon
episodes.description: The abduction of three college women from a small town has the BAU profiling an entire community, rather than an individual offender.

episodes.title: Empty Planet
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team travel to Seattle in pursuit of a bomber who is targeting places that are technologically advanced.

episodes.title: The Last Word
episodes.description: Gideon, Hotchner and their team must profile two serial killers in St. Louis who are competing to outdo each other.

episodes.title: Lessons Learned
episodes.description: Gideon, Reid, and Prentiss travel to Guantanamo Bay to profile a terrorist who has information that could prevent a major terrorist attack in the U.S.

episodes.title: Sex, Birth, Death
episodes.description: Dr. Spencer Reid suspects that a young man who has reached out to him for help may be a serial killer.

episodes.title: Profiler, Profiled
episodes.description: When Morgan is arrested for murder in Chicago, Gideon, Hotchner and the rest of the team must profile him in an attempt to prove his innocence.

episodes.title: No Way Out
episodes.description: Gideon and Morgan go head-to-head in a standoff with a prolific serial killer who is curiously calm when they corner him in a diner.

episodes.title: The Big Game
episodes.description: The big game is only beginning for the BAU when they're called to investigate the murder of a wealthy couple after their Super Bowl party.

episodes.title: Revelations
episodes.description: The BAU team races to find Reid, who has been kidnapped by a serial killer.

episodes.title: Fear and Loathing
episodes.description: The BAU team hunts a serial killer they fear is motivated by racism.

episodes.title: Distress
episodes.description: The BAU team investigates a series of random murders at construction sites in Houston.

episodes.title: Jones
episodes.description: The BAU team investigates a serial killer who was thought to have been killed during Hurricane Katrina.

episodes.title: Ashes and Dust
episodes.description: Hotch, Gideon and the BAU team link the arson victims together through corporate development firms accused of building on contaminated land.

episodes.title: Honor Among Thieves
episodes.description: Agent Prentiss's mother, a foreign ambassador, enlists the help of the team when a Russian immigrant is kidnapped and held for ransom.

episodes.title: Open Season
episodes.description: After determining that the victims had been taken from one place and transported deep into the woods, the BAU team realize their suspects hunt humans.

episodes.title: Legacy
episodes.description: After receiving a tip from a local detective, the team travels to Kansas City to investigate a report of homeless people disappearing from streets.

episodes.title: No Way Out, Part 2: The Evilution of Frank
episodes.description: Gideon takes off to hunt an elusive serial killer without telling the BAU, and the team must profile Gideon as a suspect in order to find them both.

episodes.title: Doubt
episodes.description: The BAU investigates a serial killer who is targeting women on the campus of a small Midwestern college.

episodes.title: In Name and Blood
episodes.description: The future of the BAU is in jeopardy when Hotch requests a transfer, Prentiss resigns, and Gideon goes missing.

episodes.title: Scared to Death
episodes.description: The unit tracks down a serial killer who exploits his victims' worst fears as a means to kill them.

episodes.title: Children of the Dark
episodes.description: The team investigates a crime spree that has escalated from suburban home invasions to murder.

episodes.title: Seven Seconds
episodes.description: When a child is abducted at a mall, the BAU locks down the area and profiles the people at the scene to retrieve the kid before it's too late.

episodes.title: About Face
episodes.description: The team must find a murderer who posts "Missing" fliers of his victims in advance of kidnapping and killing them.

episodes.title: Identity
episodes.description: One half of a serial-killing duo commits suicide when caught by authorities, and the BAU must race to identify his partner and save a victim.

episodes.title: Lucky
episodes.description: The pursuit of a cannibalistic serial killer forces Morgan to question his faith. Meanwhile, Garcia seemingly meets the man of her dreams.

episodes.title: Penelope
episodes.description: The team unites to determine if Garcia's life is being threatened by a serial killer.

episodes.title: True Night
episodes.description: A famous comic book artist becomes involved in the search for a serial killer in Los Angeles.

episodes.title: Birthright
episodes.description: A series of murders in rural Virginia has the BAU team investigating a link between this killing spree and a similar case two decades ago.

episodes.title: 3rd Life
episodes.description: The team profiles a serial killer who abducts two teenagers and murders one, and who will kill the other if they don't stop him in time.

episodes.title: Limelight
episodes.description: When the contents of a self-storage unit reveal the grisly early makings of a serial killer, the BAU must profile the contents in order to catch him.

episodes.title: Damaged
episodes.description: Rossi decides to revisit an unsolved case from his past and tries to unravel the circumstances behind the mysterious murder of two young parents.

episodes.title: A Higher Power
episodes.description: When suicide rate spikes in a Pittsburgh neighborhood, the BAU suspects it may be the work of a serial killer who believes he is an "Angel of Death."

episodes.title: Elephant's Memory
episodes.description: Hotchner and his team investigate a spree of killings in a small Texas town involving a teenage boy and his girlfriend.

episodes.title: In Heat
episodes.description: The BAU team travels to Miami to profile a serial killer whose sexual identity plays a key role in his choice of victims.

episodes.title: The Crossing
episodes.description: Morgan, Prentiss, Reid, and J.J. attempt to stop a stalker before he gets close to the woman who is the object of his affection.

episodes.title: Tabula Rasa
episodes.description: The BAU uses brain fingerprinting to see if a suspected killer who wakes up after long coma really doesn't remember the crimes he allegedly committed.

episodes.title: Lo-Fi
episodes.description: When people are seemingly shot at random in New York City, the BAU investigates whether a lone serial killer or a team is responsible for the spree.

episodes.title: Mayhem
episodes.description: When an SUV carrying members of the BAU explodes, the rest of the team fights to save their colleagues and catch the terrorists responsible.

episodes.title: The Angel Maker
episodes.description: When recent murders are linked to a serial killer who was executed a year ago, the BAU must find the link between him and the current killing spree.

episodes.title: Minimal Loss
episodes.description: Prentiss and Reid go undercover to investigate possible child abuse at an underground cult and get trapped inside the compound when a raid goes bad.

episodes.title: Paradise
episodes.description: A serial killer who disguises his victims' demise by creating car accidents to mask their earlier deaths is the subject of a BAU manhunt.

episodes.title: Catching Out
episodes.description: A serial killer who jumps trains and targets people living near the railway is the subject of a BAU manhunt. Meta Golding guest stars.

episodes.title: The Instincts
episodes.description: While investigating the kidnapping of a young boy in Las Vegas, Reid begins to have dreams that may help reveal buried memories from his childhood.

episodes.title: Memoriam
episodes.description: Dr. Reid embarks on his own investigation into the murder of a young boy years earlier that he believes has a connection to his childhood.

episodes.title: Masterpiece
episodes.description: The team must profile a serial killer who turns himself in, but sends them on a massive manhunt to find his latest victims before it's too late.

episodes.title: 52 Pickup
episodes.description: Agents Prentiss and Todd go undercover to profile a pickup artist who uses his skills of persuasion to lure women into danger.

episodes.title: Brothers in Arms
episodes.description: A BAU case hits close to home for Morgan when a serial killer specifically focuses on members of the police force in Phoenix, Ariz.

episodes.title: Normal
episodes.description: The team investigates a serial killer who kills luxury car owners while they are driving on freeways in Southern California.

episodes.title: Soul Mates
episodes.description: The BAU team suspects a member of an affluent community in Atlanta is responsible for the disappearance of a local young woman.

episodes.title: Bloodline
episodes.description: The BAU team becomes involved in the case of a family working together to abduct young women.

episodes.title: Cold Comfort
episodes.description: Agents Hotchner and Rossi track a suspect who abducts, kills and embalms his victims in order to spend more time with them.

episodes.title: Zoe's Reprise
episodes.description: The team pursues a copycat serial killer who is re-creating the techniques used by past famous murderers.

episodes.title: Pleasure Is My Business
episodes.description: The team searches for a female suspect who uses her professional skills as a high-class call girl to lure and kill high-powered executives.

episodes.title: Demonology
episodes.description: Agent Prentiss has a personal connection to one of the victims in a series of deaths with religious overtones.

episodes.title: Omnivore
episodes.description: Hotch revisits the first case he worked at the BAU when one of the deadliest serial killers in New England's history strikes after a 10-year hiatus.

episodes.title: House on Fire
episodes.description: The BAU team must track down a serial arsonist who instills fear in a small town by setting fire to community meeting places.

episodes.title: Conflicted
episodes.description: The team travels to South Padre Island during spring break to find a serial killer who is targeting college students on vacation.

episodes.title: A Shade of Gray
episodes.description: When profiling a series of child murders, the team discovers that one of the cases may not be the handiwork of the serial killer they apprehended.

episodes.title: The Big Wheel
episodes.description: When the team is sent a videotape from a serial killer, they discover a hidden message asking them to help him stop his murderous ways.

episodes.title: Roadkill
episodes.description: An unknown subject who kills with his car is the subject of a BAU investigation.

episodes.title: Amplification
episodes.description: When a new type of chemical warfare is released into the open air, the BAU must act quickly to find the source before any more people are exposed.

episodes.title: To Hell..
episodes.description: The BAU tracks a serial killer who takes junkies, prostitutes, and the homeless across the border into Canada, and an agent's life is in peril.

episodes.title: ...And Back
episodes.description: The BAU tracks a serial killer who takes junkies, prostitutes, and the homeless across the border into Canada, and an agent's life is in peril.

episodes.title: Faceless, Nameless
episodes.description: Hotch's unexplained absence quickly becomes apparent when the team is called back together to profile a killer who is targeting an ER doctor.

episodes.title: Haunted
episodes.description: When a disturbed man kills several people at a pharmacy, the BAU must figure out what triggered his actions before he hurts anyone else.

episodes.title: Reckoner
episodes.description: The BAU investigates a case in Rossi's hometown that involves both his personal and professional life.

episodes.title: Hopeless
episodes.description: The BAU investigates a group of thrill-seeking suspects with a pack mentality who are randomly selecting their victims in the nation's capital.

episodes.title: Cradle to Grave
episodes.description: The team hunts a suspect who impregnates his victims and then forces them to give birth before murdering them.

episodes.title: The Eyes Have It
episodes.description: The BAU team tracks a serial killer who keeps the eyes of his victims as souvenirs.

episodes.title: The Performer
episodes.description: The BAU team follows a trail of murders that seems to align with the tour schedule of a strange rock star.

episodes.title: Outfoxed
episodes.description: While tracking a family annihilator, the BAU must seek advice from one of the most horrific killers from the team's past.
The BAU team races to help Hotchner find The Reaper and save his family before it's too late.

episodes.title: The Slave Of Duty
episodes.description: While Agent Hotchner takes a leave of absence from the BAU, the team must regroup to solve a home invasion case.

episodes.title: Retaliation
episodes.description: The BAU must profile a criminal's past in order to catch him after he escapes from custody and begins a killing spree.

episodes.title: The Uncanny Valley
episodes.description: An unusual personal obsession is at the center of a BAU abduction case. Meanwhile, Hotch struggles with his return to work.

episodes.title: Risky Business
episodes.description: A rash of startling teen suicides in a small Wyoming town is the focus of a BAU investigation.

episodes.title: Parasite
episodes.description: The BAU follows the mental decline of a con artist whose schemes have become so complicated that he begins to eliminate the people involved in them.

episodes.title: Public Enemy
episodes.description: A serial killer who targets random victims in highly visible places to create a sense of public fear is the subject of a BAU investigation.

episodes.title: Mosley Lane
episodes.description: The BAU profiles a child abductor who may have been keeping children for more than eight years.

episodes.title: Solitary Man
episodes.description: A truck driver is kidnapping women and disposing of them in random locations, and the BAU must find out his motive in order to catch him.

episodes.title: The Fight
episodes.description: The team travels to San Francisco to investigate the murders of several homeless men and teams up with a separate BAU group.

episodes.title: Rite Of Passage
episodes.description: The BAU team heads to Texas to track a serial killer targeting illegal immigrants who are attempting to make safe passage into the United States.

episodes.title: ...A Thousand Words
episodes.description: The BAU team must profile a serial killer covered in tattoos who commits suicide, but leaves clues to the whereabouts of his last victim.

episodes.title: Exit Wounds
episodes.description: Garcia plays a crucial role in a case when she travels to Alaska with the BAU team to investigate the murders of several residents of a small town.

episodes.title: The Internet Is Forever
episodes.description: The BAU team profiles a serial killer who uses the Internet as his hunting ground, bringing a whole new meaning to the term "social networking."

episodes.title: Our Darkest Hour
episodes.description: A series of rolling blackouts in Los Angeles lures a serial killer out of hiding, giving him renewed opportunities to continue his killing spree.

episodes.title: Longest Night
episodes.description: The BAU team closes in on the serial killer as he continues his murder spree throughout Los Angeles - with Spicer's kidnapped daughter as his hostage.

episodes.title: JJ
episodes.description: While JJ attempts to reunite a family whose daughter has mysteriously disappeared, her BAU family braces for the loss of one of their own.

episodes.title: Remembrance Of Things Past
episodes.description: When several women are found murdered in a similar fashion, Rossi revisits a cold case that has haunted him for 25 years.

episodes.title: Compromising Positions
episodes.description: The BAU team searches for a serial killer who is preying on married couples.¬†Also, Hotchner looks to one of the team to fill JJ's vacant role.

episodes.title: Safe Haven
episodes.description: The BAU team is on the trail of a serial killer targeting families throughout the Midwest.

episodes.title: Devil's Night
episodes.description: The BAU team must find a killer who has struck Detroit for the past three years solely during the raucous pre-Halloween celebration Devil's Night.

episodes.title: Middle Man
episodes.description: When bodies begin turning up in the cornfields of Indiana, the BAU team must catch a pack of serial killers targeting exotic dancers.

episodes.title: Reflection Of Desire
episodes.description: When a kidnapped woman is found murdered in an alley in Georgetown, the BAU team goes on the hunt for the killer before he can strike again.

episodes.title: Into The Woods
episodes.description: When a 10-year-old is found murdered on the Appalachian Trail, the BAU goes deep into its forests in search of a man lurking in the wilderness.

episodes.title: What Happens At Home...
episodes.description: The BAU searches inside a gated New Mexico community for a killer targeting women, and Hotch looks to an FBI cadet with a unique past for help.

episodes.title: 25 To Life
episodes.description: Morgan suggests that a prisoner is ready for parole, but later regrets his decision when the man murders someone days after being released.

episodes.title: Corazon
episodes.description: As the BAU travels to Miami to investigate a series of bizarre, ritualistic murders, Reid suffers a series of blinding headaches and hallucinations.

episodes.title: The Thirteenth Step
episodes.description: The BAU hits the road to track down a pair of young lovers on an interstate murder spree, and Prentiss hears frightening news from her former boss.

episodes.title: Sense Memory
episodes.description: The BAU travels to Los Angeles to investigate unusual murders throughout the city. Also, more of Prentiss's mysterious past comes to light.

episodes.title: Today I Do
episodes.description: The BAU is called to upstate New York to investigate mysterious disappearances.

episodes.title: Coda
episodes.description: Reid makes a connection with an autistic child that could assist the BAU in finding the boy's missing parents.

episodes.title: Valhalla
episodes.description: After a series of suspicious murders occur, Prentiss suspects her old Interpol nemesis.

episodes.title: Lauren
episodes.description: Prentiss is ready to confront her nemesis, Ian Doyle, once and for all.

episodes.title: With Friends Like These..
episodes.description: When a gang of suspected murderers begins targeting a new victim each night, the BAU travels to Portland to head them off.

episodes.title: Hanley Waters
episodes.description: As the BAU investigates targeted killings in Tampa, they also deal with their own feelings about the loss of Prentiss.

episodes.title: The Stranger
episodes.description: The BAU hunts a stalker in San Diego who is targeting college students. Meanwhile, the team comes under scrutiny in the wake of the loss of Prentiss.

episodes.title: Out Of The Light
episodes.description: The BAU is called to a North Carolina mountain town after a woman is found badly injured and another is missing.

episodes.title: Big Sea
episodes.description: The BAU is Florida-bound to investigate bodies discovered buried in the ocean floor, but the case suddenly hits close to home for Morgan.

episodes.title: Supply & Demand
episodes.description: The bodies of two missing persons are found in a car trunk, and the BAU suspects that an interstate human trafficking ring is at work.

episodes.title: It Takes A Village
episodes.description: The BAU team is at a crossroads as they are questioned by a Senate Committee for their retaliatory actions in the wake of Prentiss' loss, but an unexpected familiar face could help them win their case and keep the team together.

episodes.title: Proof
episodes.description: The BAU team searches rural Oklahoma when women are being found murdered after being robbed of one of their five senses. Also, JJ and Prentiss get the cold shoulder from Reid as he deals with their deception about Prentiss' presumed death.

episodes.title: Dorado Falls
episodes.description: The BAU team investigates a mass murder at an Internet security company in Charlottesville, Va., but clues reveal it is not a typical serial killer at work. Also, Prentiss must complete recertification training under Morgan's watchful eye.

episodes.title: Painless
episodes.description: Survivors of a Boise high school massacre return to remember the event 10 years later, but the BAU team is called in when a new killer with a similar style targets the survivors.

episodes.title: From Childhood's Hour
episodes.description: The BAU team searches for children being abducted in St. Louis, and Rossi receives shocking news from his first wife.

episodes.title: Epilogue
episodes.description: The BAU team searches a California mountain lake when bodies mysteriously turn up there, and Rossi struggles with a decision regarding his ex-wife.

episodes.title: There's No Place Like Home
episodes.description: After a series of tornadoes hit Kansas, the BAU searches Wichita when bodies turn up in the aftermath of the storms, and JJ faces pressure on both the work and home fronts.

episodes.title: Hope
episodes.description: A case turns personal for Garcia when a friend of hers goes missing seven years to the day after her daughter disappeared.

episodes.title: Self-Fulfilling Prophecy
episodes.description: The BAU team investigates the real reason behind an apparent mass suicide at a military academy.

episodes.title: The Bittersweet Science
episodes.description: The BAU searches the boxing scene in Philadelphia for a killer with a blood lust, and hotch makes a connection with a fellow triathlete.

episodes.title: True Genius
episodes.description: A series of murders in San Francisco bearing the marks of the infamous Zodiac Killer have the BAUwondering if the notorious serial killer is back.

episodes.title: Unknown Subject
episodes.description: The BAU team finds discord in Houston when a rapist known as "the piano man" returns to assault his previous victims.

episodes.title: Snake Eyes
episodes.description: The BAU team tries to beat the house when they investigate a series of casino-related murders in Atlantic city, and Garcia wonders if she and Morgan became too friendly after a fight with her boyfriend.

episodes.title: Closing Time
episodes.description: The BAU team hits some rough surf when they investigate bodies found in southern California lifeguard towers.

episodes.title: A Thin Line
episodes.description: When brutal home invasions in the California suburbs appear gang-related, the BAU team thinks that more devious motives could be at work.

episodes.title: A Family Affair
episodes.description: The heat is on in Atlanta when the BAU investigates murders of women and realizes they're looking for more than one unsub.

episodes.title: I Love You, Tommy Brown
episodes.description: The BAU team investigates the murders of married couples in Seattle, and Garcia fears a proposal from Kevin is imminent.

episodes.title: Foundation
episodes.description: When a young boy is found wandering in the Arizona desert and another child disappears, the BAU team goes on the hunt for the kidnapper.

episodes.title: Heathridge Manor
episodes.description: The BAU is in for a ghost of a time when the team investigates a series of ritualistic murders in Oregon.

episodes.title: The Company
episodes.description: When his missing cousin reappears, Morgan is forced to confront a lie he told to protect his family and makes the BAU team reopen the file on her disappearance.

episodes.title: Divining Rod
episodes.description: When a serial murderer is executed, a copycat emerges in Oklahoma, and the BAU team must act swiftly.

episodes.title: Profiling 101
episodes.description: Rossi and the team teach college students about the science of criminal profiling, as they look back on a serial killing case that spanned nearly 20 years.

episodes.title: Hit
episodes.description: The BAU goes up against a gang of bank robbing serial killers, and the stakes rise when one of their own becomes a hostage, on the first part of the two-hour seventh season finale.

episodes.title: Run
episodes.description: The BAU continues to negotiate with the serial killing bank robbers, one of the team gets married and Prentiss ponders her future, on the conclusion of the two-hour seventh season finale.

episodes.title: The Silencer
episodes.description: The team tracks an escaped Texas inmate whose victims bear his unique trademark: Their mouths are sewn shut.

episodes.title: The Pact
episodes.description: When the bodies of two ostensibly unrelated victims are discovered, the team suspects that two killers worked together to carry out the murders.

episodes.title: Through the Looking Glass
episodes.description: The team races against time to find a connection between two Kansas families -- one murdered and the other abducted.

episodes.title: God Complex
episodes.description: When a legless body is discovered in the New Mexico desert, the team is brought in to pursue a surgeon who's performing needless amputations.

episodes.title: The Good Earth
episodes.description: When four men disappear in rural Oregon, the team attempts to track them down by finding a common link among them.

episodes.title: The Apprenticeship
episodes.description: When hookers in Miami are murdered in a style similar to a rash of animal slayings, the team must work fast to find the increasingly confident killer.

episodes.title: The Fallen
episodes.description: The team travels to Santa Monica, Calif., when the burned bodies of homeless people turn up near the city's famous pier.

episodes.title: The Wheels on the Bus..
episodes.description: The team goes in search of a school bus full of students that has vanished near Washington, D.C.

episodes.title: Magnificent Light
episodes.description: When a follower of a well-known motivational speaker is murdered in Seattle, the team suspects the orator -- until he vanishes.

episodes.title: The Lesson
episodes.description: A number of male bodies disposed of in bizarre, ritualistic ways sends the team to Winslow, Ariz., in search of the killer.

episodes.title: Perennials
episodes.description: The team travels south to investigate a suspect whose signature is identical to that of a serial killer whose crimes were committed 30 years earlier.

episodes.title: Zugzwang
episodes.description: When Reid learns that his girlfriend has been abducted by her stalker, he and the team band together to save her before it's too late.

episodes.title: Magnum Opus
episodes.description: While Reid copes with a personal loss, the rest of the team goes to San Francisco to investigate a string of murders in the Mission District.

episodes.title: All That Remains
episodes.description: The team heads to Maryland to profile an author whose wife mysteriously disappeared a year ago -- and whose daughters have just vanished.

episodes.title: Broken
episodes.description: The team investigates when murder victims in Austin, Texas, are found with their watches set incorrectly -- a clue that may link the crimes.

episodes.title: Carbon Copy
episodes.description: The team gets a break in their pursuit of the Replicator -- the BAU's stalker -- when murder victims turn up in Philadelphia.

episodes.title: The Gathering
episodes.description: In St. Paul, Minn., the team investigates the murders of people who were documenting their personal lives and desires on blogs and social media.

episodes.title: Restoration
episodes.description: While on the trail of a killer in Chicago, Morgan comes to believe that the suspect may be linked to the person who molested him as a child.

episodes.title: Pay It Forward
episodes.description: When the opening of a time capsule results in a grisly discovery, the team looks into a potential link to a police officer's death.

episodes.title: Alchemy
episodes.description: The ritualistic murder and dismemberment of two young males sends the team to Rapid City, S.D., to investigate.

episodes.title: Nanny Dearest
episodes.description: In Los Angeles, the team profiles a suspect who abducts nannies and the children in their care on the same date every year.
The team heads to Detroit to probe a pair of murders in which the victims ended up in the trunks of their vehicles.

episodes.title: Brothers Hotchner
episodes.description: When the team probes a series of deaths tied to apparent ecstasy overdoses, Hotch learns that his estranged brother may be involved.

episodes.title: The Replicator
episodes.description: When the Replicator targets a team member as his next victim, the unit must thwart the cunning killer before he can carry out his end game.

episodes.title: The Inspiration: Part 1
episodes.description: The BAU searches for a serial killer in Glendale, Arizona, and the team believes that Hotch is being groomed to replace the late Erin Strauss.

episodes.title: The Inspiration: Part 2
episodes.description: As the BAU close in on the culprit in ritualistic murders in Arizona, they encounter their suspect's mother, who is obviously keeping secrets.

episodes.title: Final Shot
episodes.description: Sniper attacks in Dallas lead the BAU to consider that the incident is motivated by the approaching anniversary of the Kennedy assassination.

episodes.title: To Bear Witness
episodes.description: Mateo Cruz is named section chief over the BAU as the team hunts for a sadistic perp in Baltimore who renders his victims unable to communicate.

episodes.title: Route 66
episodes.description: As a critically wounded Hotch hallucinates moments from his past, the BAU question a man whose estranged teenage daughter has disappeared.

episodes.title: In the Blood
episodes.description: Clues in a series of ritualistic murders in Utah remind the BAU of the Salem witch trials, and Garcia hosts a Day of the Dead party.

episodes.title: Gatekeeper
episodes.description: The BAU searches for a common trait among Boston strangling victims, and Rossi mourns the impending closure of his favorite bar.

episodes.title: The Return
episodes.description: The BAU thinks that missing Chicago teens may be behind a killing spree; Morgan has a hard time accepting his girlfriend's devotion to her work.

episodes.title: Strange Fruit
episodes.description: Shameful family secrets come to light when human remains turn up in the backyard of a home in Virginia.

episodes.title: The Caller
episodes.description: When a young boy disappears from his St. Louis home, the BAU finds connections to a cold case from years earlier.

episodes.title: Bully
episodes.description: A BAU investigation into a string of murders in Kansas City reunites Blake with her estranged father, a retired cop, and brother, a detective.

episodes.title: The Black Queen
episodes.description: Garcia reconnects with an old flame and fellow hacker in hopes of getting help with a BAU murder investigation in San Jose.

episodes.title: The Road Home
episodes.description: Rossi leaves for Los Angeles to search for his former Marine sergeant, who's vanished, while the rest of the BAU searches for a killer in Cleveland.
When JJ is kidnapped, the BAU calls in Prentiss to assist and searches for leads in her missions for the state department.

episodes.title: Mr. and Mrs. Anderson
episodes.description: The BAU realizes that they're actually looking for two culprits in a string of murders in Pittsburgh; Garcia and Morgan make Valentine's Day plans.

episodes.title: Gabby
episodes.description: The BAU reveals some shocking family secrets while investigating the disappearance of a four-year-old girl from a relative's home in Mississippi.

episodes.title: Persuasion
episodes.description: The BAU investigates when a series of bodies turn up in the middle of the Las Vegas desert -- all victims of drowning.

episodes.title: Rabid
episodes.description: Bodies covered with bite marks -- both animal and human -- turn up in a shallow grave outside Milwaukee; Garcia and Reid prepare for a fitness exam.

episodes.title: The Edge of Winter
episodes.description: The BAU is closing an investigation into a stabbing spree in upstate New York when the lone survivor offers information that changes everything.

episodes.title: Blood Relations
episodes.description: The BAU discovers a long-standing feud between a pair of rural clans when two bodies are found in the backwoods of West Virginia.

episodes.title: What Happens in Mecklinburg
episodes.description: The BAU looks for a common element in a series of abductions in Memphis; Savannah confronts Morgan about being gone all the time.

episodes.title: Fatal
episodes.description: A killer with a penchant for ancient Greek philosophy brings the BAU to Long Beach, California, and Hotch prepares for Jack's third grade Career Day.

episodes.title: Angels
episodes.description: The BAU members are caught in the crossfire while investigating the religiously motivated murders of several prostitutes in Texas.

episodes.title: Demons
episodes.description: As they dig deeper into the Texas prostitute murders, the BAU discovers that the killer has a greater -- and much deadlier -- ambition.

episodes.title: X
episodes.description: An undercover agent from the sex crimes unit joins the team in search of a killer who's littering the California desert with dismembered torsos.

episodes.title: Burn
episodes.description: In Seattle, the team hunts down a bizarre killer who carves roman numerals into his victims' mouths; Garcia attends an execution.

episodes.title: A Thousand Suns
episodes.description: When a commercial jet full of passengers crashes in a Colorado field, the team discovers that the plane was brought down by remote control.

episodes.title: The Itch
episodes.description: The team probes the death of an investigative journalist who walked into oncoming traffic and had mysterious scars and scratches on his body.

episodes.title: Boxed In
episodes.description: The team goes to San Diego to investigate the sudden reappearance of a boy who vanished on Halloween one year earlier and was held captive in a box.

episodes.title: If the Shoe Fits
episodes.description: The team goes to Montana, where three young men are found dead with cell phones stuffed in their mouths with the alarms set to go off at midnight.

episodes.title: Hashtag
episodes.description: The team looks into the murder of a teen whose corpse appears in a selfie on social media sites; Morgan struggles to find private time with Savannah.

episodes.title: The Boys of Sudworth Place
episodes.description: When a defense attorney known for working with troubled youth is abducted, the team wonders if the disappearance is linked to one of his cases.

episodes.title: Fate
episodes.description: The team is called to Virginia, where victims are being brutally stabbed, then neatly displayed in fresh clothes; Rossi receives a surprising visitor.

episodes.title: Amelia Porter
episodes.description: In Salt Lake City, the team investigates a triple homicide that puts them on the trail of a fugitive who disappeared after committing a grisly crime.

episodes.title: The Forever People
episodes.description: In Boulder City, Nevada, the team looks for a serial killer amidst a cult that freezes members as part of their induction ritual.

episodes.title: Anonymous
episodes.description: When a string of seemingly unrelated murders occurs in Tallahassee, the team learns the victims were all organ donors; Rossi loses a close friend.

episodes.title: Nelson's Sparrow
episodes.description: A case hits home for Rossi when a colleague from his past is found murdered, setting him on the trail of a bird-obsessed serial killer.

episodes.title: Hero Worship
episodes.description: When an Indianapolis coffee shop explodes and the media rallies around a local hero, the team's seemingly open-and-shut case could go up in smoke.

episodes.title: Scream
episodes.description: The team is called in to investigate the deaths of two California women found in dumpsters with their bodies beaten and throats slashed.

episodes.title: Lockdown
episodes.description: The warden of a maximum security prison calls on the team when two guards are murdered, but more danger looms when the trouble escalates into a riot.

episodes.title: Breath Play
episodes.description: In Wisconsin, the team hunts for a serial killer whose victims are obsessed with a best-selling erotic novel; Kate suspects her niece has a secret.

episodes.title: Rock Creek Park
episodes.description: When the wife of a junior congressman is abducted, the unit discovers that the motives behind the crime are not what the FBI suspects.

episodes.title: Beyond Borders
episodes.description: When a family on vacation in the Caribbean is abducted, the team is called upon to assist Special Agent Jack Garrett and his team in Barbados.

episodes.title: A Place at the Table
episodes.description: The team investigates the murder of a family found dead at their dining room table; Hotch helps Jessica keep Roy out of a nursing home.

episodes.title: Mr. Scratch
episodes.description: The unit searches for a criminal who puts his victims into a violent hallucinogenic state, causing them to kill their loved ones.

episodes.title: Protection
episodes.description: The team takes the case of a delusional killer who believes he is punishing criminals; Kate's niece sneaks out at night with a stranger.

episodes.title: The Hunt
episodes.description: When Kate's niece and her friend are kidnapped, the team rushes to find them before they become victims of traffickers.

episodes.title: The Job
episodes.description: As the BAU searches for a serial killer who paints his victims' faces, prospective new team member Tara Lewis gets a chance to show off her skills.

episodes.title: The Witness
episodes.description: A poison gas attack on a commuter bus brings the team to L.A., where they zero in on a businessman who was late to work and is acting strangely.

episodes.title: 'Til Death Do Us Part
episodes.description: The murder of two brides-to-be in Savannah, Georgia, leaves the team looking for a jilted lover. But a third body forces them to rethink the profile.

episodes.title: Outlaw
episodes.description: When three teens are found slain in a New Mexico restaurant, the team sees uncanny similarities to a cold case from six years ago.
