episodes.title: The Night Watch
episodes.description: An elaborate murder scene triggers a search for a street artist whose identity is a well-kept secret. Work takes a toll on Lewis's home life.

episodes.title: Pariahville
episodes.description: A killing in a town populated by sex offenders presents a daunting challenge for the team. Meanwhile, Lewis receives a tempting job offer.

episodes.title: Target Rich
episodes.description: As the team celebrates JJ's return, Rossi's daughter begs for help finding a missing college student. An interview with Montolo takes a dramatic turn.

episodes.title: Awake
episodes.description: The BAU races to track down a man who's abducting and torturing victims along a Phoenix highway. A threat forces Garcia to bunk down at the office.

episodes.title: Internal Affairs
episodes.description: After an attack on undercover DEA agents in Texas, the NSA calls in Hotch's team to investigate an online drug cartel and root out an agency mole.

episodes.title: Future Perfect
episodes.description: Two bodies found with strange markings in Florida spur a hunt for a suspect with medical knowledge and a morbid fixation.

episodes.title: Entropy
episodes.description: As the team closes in on the network of hitmen threatening Garcia, Reid becomes locked in a high-stakes showdown with a woman known as "Miss .45."

episodes.title: Drive
episodes.description: The BAU traces a series of headless bodies in Boston to a ride-sharing service. But there's something more that the victims have in common.

episodes.title: The Bond
episodes.description: While the team struggles to connect the dots between several truck stop killings, a troubled man reconnects with his long-lost biological mother.

episodes.title: Hostage
episodes.description: After an 18-year-old escapes from a basement where she's been held captive for years, the race is on to find her tormentor and his other victims.

episodes.title: A Badge and a Gun
episodes.description: Adding up clues from several suffocations in L.A., the team begins to fear the killer is a rogue FBI agent. A text from Savannah puts Morgan on edge.

episodes.title: Derek
episodes.description: To survive an agonizing ordeal, Morgan slips into a trance, where he connects with his late father and realizes what Savannah wanted to tell him.

episodes.title: The Sandman
episodes.description: The BAU welcomes Morgan back after a six-month leave, but the celebration is cut short by news of a ritualistic family murder in Kansas.

episodes.title: A Beautiful Disaster
episodes.description: On a quest to find out who targeted Morgan and Savannah, the team uncovers links to a past case. A note from the sniper leads to a harrowing showdown.

episodes.title: Tribute
episodes.description: Emily Prentiss reunites with the BAU to track down a murderer who's mimicking crimes by famous serial killers like Jack the Ripper and Son of Sam.

episodes.title: Inner Beauty
episodes.description: The team tries to figure out what drives a killer to disfigure his female victims' faces. Rossi reconnects with someone from his past.

episodes.title: Devil's Backbone
episodes.description: A notorious female serial killer draws the members of the BAU into a twisted mind game when they ask her for help finding two missing boys.

episodes.title: The Storm
episodes.description: When Hotch is arrested in a SWAT raid, the team scrambles to clear his name, but they soon realize it's part of a larger plot that's unfolding fast.

episodes.title: The Crimson King
episodes.description: A new agent, Luke Alvez, joins the team to help them catch the Crimson King, one of the escaped killers from last season.

episodes.title: Sick Day
episodes.description: Fresh from the tragic aftermath of a child abduction case, a vulnerable JJ returns home to find that her youngest child is sick.

episodes.title: Taboo
episodes.description: The gruesome murder of three single mothers leads to an investigation of what they had in common and why they were killed.

episodes.title: Keeper
episodes.description: The body parts of several people who had gone missing over a period of six months are discovered in a homeless man's shopping cart.

episodes.title: The Anti-Terrorism Squad
episodes.description: A 17-year-old girl returns home, well past her curfew, to run into the dead bodies of her family members, who have been shot execution-style.

episodes.title: Elliott's Pond
episodes.description: The team is called in to investigate after three children go missing in the same area where two children disappeared 30 years ago.

episodes.title: Mirror Image
episodes.description: The team launches an investigation into the sudden arrival of a mysterious man claiming to be Tara's younger brother, Gabriel.

episodes.title: Scarecrow
episodes.description: The team heads to Yakima, Washington, after a local girl goes missing and the remains of several people are found along a creek bed.

episodes.title: Profiling 202
episodes.description: A familiar voice from the past calls Rossi on his birthday to inform him that he has abducted a woman, and he has more information to share.

episodes.title: Seek & Destroy
episodes.description: The team investigates a series of brutal, destructive home invasions that end in murder in upscale San Diego neighborhoods.

episodes.title: Surface Tension
episodes.description: While dissecting a corpse in an anatomy class, a teacher and her students discover a strange mark that was found on another dead body.

episodes.title: A Good Husband
episodes.description: The discoveries of two male torsos within close proximity of each other in Palm Springs appear to point to a single killer.

episodes.title: Spencer
episodes.description: Spencer is arrested near the U.S.-Mexico border, after a stash of heroin is discovered in the trunk of the vehicle that he's driving.

episodes.title: Collision Course
episodes.description: Two pedestrians are run down on the same road by two similar vehicles, leading the team to wonder if the incidents point to a pattern.

episodes.title: Alpha Male
episodes.description: With Spencer's incarceration at the back of their minds, the BAU heads to Philadelphia to investigate a series of acid attacks.

episodes.title: Assistance is Futile
episodes.description: A number of corpses are found in New York City, victims of a serial killer with an evident fondness for breaking bones.

episodes.title: In the Dark
episodes.description: A series of home invasion stabbings and shootings of hunters in Vermont have the team wondering if they are dealing with two killers.

episodes.title: Hell's Kitchen
episodes.description: A girl's disappearance in New York City just before her 16th birthday appears to have similarities to two previous abduction killings.

episodes.title: True North
episodes.description: The dead bodies of three victims are discovered tied to stakes in the Arizona desert, and in varying stages of decomposition.

episodes.title: Unforgettable
episodes.description: Stephen's friend from the BAP is hospitalized following what looks like a heart attack but it turns out to be something more.

episodes.title: Green Light
episodes.description: The victim of one of the team's former cases turns up, posing as a nurse to Spencer's mother, shortly before the latter disappears.

episodes.title: Red Light
episodes.description: Reid finds himself returning to prison for an unusual t√™te-√†-t√™te with the accomplice of the girl who abducted his mother.

episodes.title: Space Pilot 3000
episodes.description: A pizza delivery boy named Fry awakens from a state of suspended animation and finds himself in a futuristic world populated by aliens, robots and spaceships.

episodes.title: The Series Has Landed
episodes.description: Fry eagerly anticipates his first visit to the moon...only to realize that it is home to a cheesy amusement park.

episodes.title: I, Roommate
episodes.description: Fry and Bender become a futuristic odd couple when they attempt to share an apartment.

episodes.title: Love's Labours Lost In Space
episodes.description: Leela finds herself the object of a starship captain's amorous advances.

episodes.title: Fear of a Bot Planet
episodes.description: Fry and Lela find themselves trapped on a planet ruled by human-hating robots.

episodes.title: A Fishful of Dollars
episodes.description: Fry discovers that a small amount of money left in his old bank account has accumulated into a fortune. But his nostalgia for all things 20th century puts him at odds with an evil oil tycoon.

episodes.title: My Three Suns
episodes.description: The crew visits a planet inhabited by liquid aliens. Fry, after delivering a package under the scorching heat of the planet's three suns, finds a bottle of cool blue liquid to quench his thirst. But when that liquid turns out to be the civilization's ruler, Fry finds he has become the new leader. Initially drunk with power, he soon discovers his life is in danger and must turn to his friends to help him dry out.

episodes.title: A Big Piece of Garbage
episodes.description: A gigantic ball of garbage carelessly launched off Earth in the 21st century returns on a collision course for New New York City and Fry and the crew set out on a mission to destroy it.

episodes.title: Hell Is Other Robots
episodes.description: Bender seeks religion after becoming addicted to electricity.

episodes.title: A Flight to Remember
episodes.description: Ep10 - As the Planet Express team vacations aboard the starship Titanic, the vessel falls victim to the gravitational pull of a black hole.

episodes.title: Mars University
episodes.description: Fry enrolls in Mars University, only to discover that his dorm roommate is a super intelligent monkey; Bender teaches a fraternity of robots how to be cool.

episodes.title: When Aliens Attack
episodes.description: Fry and his friends fight off an alien invasion of Earth by recreating a television drama from the 20th century featuring a sexily-attired single female lawyer.

episodes.title: Fry and the Slurm Factory
episodes.description: Fry wins a contest that takes the crew on a tour of the Slurm factory...and exposes its terrible secret.

episodes.title: I Second That Emotion
episodes.description: After Bender flushes Nibbler down a toilet, Fry, Leela and Bender journey through a sewer system inhabited by mutants.

episodes.title: Brannigan, Begin Again
episodes.description: After being court-martialed Zap Brannigan joins the Planet Express team...only to inspire Fry and Bender to mutiny against Leela.

episodes.title: A Head in the Polls
episodes.description: When the price of titanium skyrockets, Bender hocks his titanium-rich body to a pawnshop and lives the good life, until Richard Nixon s head uses the robot's torso to stage a political comeback.

episodes.title: Xmas Story
episodes.description: Fry and Leela find themselves targeted by a murderous robotic Santa Claus; Bender volunteers at a shelter for homeless robots.

episodes.title: Why Must I Be a Crustacean in Love
episodes.description: When Zoidberg runs amok during mating season, Fry sets out to teach him how to woo a mate.

episodes.title: Put Your Head on My Shoulders
episodes.description: Valentine's Day turns into a nightmare for Fry after his head is surgically attached to Amy's body.

episodes.title: The Lesser of Two Evils
episodes.description: Fry fears the worst when Bender's exact duplicate joins the crew on a mission to deliver a valuable atomic tiara to The Miss Universe pageant.

episodes.title: Raging Bender
episodes.description: Bender's popularity soars when he becomes a successful pro-wrestler, but when he is instructed to lose a fight, Leela steps into help him defeat an opponent trained by her old master.

episodes.title: A Bicyclops Built for Two
episodes.description: Leela finally encounters another member of her race, a handsome male. But when he turns out to be a jerk, she fears that leaving him will mean her species' extinction.

episodes.title: How Hermes Requisitioned His Groove Back
episodes.description: Hermes grows despondent when he misses an opportunity for a promotion; a female bureaucrat is turned-on by Fry's sloppiness.

episodes.title: A Clone of My Own
episodes.description: The Professor chooses his clone, Cubert, as the successor to his research...only to realize that Cubert has dreams of his own.

episodes.title: The Deep South
episodes.description: Deep beneath the ocean, the crew discovers the lost city of Atlantis where Fry falls hopelessly in love with mermaid.

episodes.title: Bender Gets Made
episodes.description: After joining the robot Mafia, Bender finds himself involved in scheme to loot the Planet Express spaceship of its cargo and destroy the crew.

episodes.title: The Problem With Popplers
episodes.description: Powerful alien beings threaten to devour of all mankind after the Planet Express crew inadvertently introduces earthlings to the aliens' tasty offspring.

episodes.title: Mother's Day
episodes.description: On Mother's Day, Mom unleashes hoard of rampaging robots to destroy the Earth-and only the Professor can stop them.

episodes.title: Anthology of Interest I
episodes.description: The Professor's "What-If" machine simulates Bender, Leela and Fry's wishes: Bender turns into a giant robot; Leela impulsively murders her friends; Vice President Al Gore, Stephen Hawking, Gary Gygax, and Nichelle Nichols come to the rescue when Fry inadvertently opens a rip in the space-time continuum.

episodes.title: The Honking
episodes.description: When Bender inherits a castle from his deceased uncle, he finds himself being pursued by a terrifying, driverless car.

episodes.title: War is the H-Word
episodes.description: Fry and Bender face off against an army of aliens on a far-off planet after they join the army to qualify for military discounts.

episodes.title: The Cryonic Woman
episodes.description: A woman from Fry's past unthaws in the year 3000, but when she feels out of place, she and Fry journey a thousand years into the future.

episodes.title: Parasites Lost
episodes.description: A miniature version of the Planet Express crew attempts to rid Fry's body of parasitic worms; meanwhile, Leela finds Fry's new personality irresistible.

episodes.title: Amazon Women in the Mood
episodes.description: Fry and the others find themselves trapped on a planet of Amazonian women ruled by a man-hating computer.

episodes.title: Bendless Love
episodes.description: Bender finds true romance with a coworker after crossing a picket line, but jealousy over his love's ex-boyfriend threatens to destroy everything.

episodes.title: The Day the Earth Stood Stupid
episodes.description: Only Fry can save Earth when evil brains from another world plot to make everyone stupid.

episodes.title: That's Lobstertainment!
episodes.description: Dr. Zoidberg promises his uncle-washed-up comedian Harold Zoid-that he will invest a million dollars in his Hollywood movie.

episodes.title: The Birdbot of Ice-Catraz
episodes.description: Leela fights to save the lives of penguins after the Planet Express ship is involved in an oil spill on Pluto.

episodes.title: The Luck of the Fryrish
episodes.description: Fry searches the ancient ruins of Old New York for his beloved lucky clover...only to conclude that his older brother stole not only the clover-but his life.

episodes.title: The Cyber House Rules
episodes.description: Tired of feeling like an outcast, Leela has a second eye grafted onto her face; Bender adopts twelve children after learning about the government's seemingly lucrative stipend.

episodes.title: Insane in the Mainframe
episodes.description: Fry and Bender become inadvertent participants in a bank robbery and are sentenced to a robot insane asylum where Fry comes to believe that he is indeed a robot.

episodes.title: Bendin' in the Wind

episodes.title: Anthology of Interest II
episodes.description: The What-If Machine tells Bender what it would be like if he were human, Fry what it would be like if life were like a video game, and Leela what it would be like if she found her true home.

episodes.description: Bender accidentally gets shot out into the heavens and becomes god to a race of tiny aliens only to fail in that position and meet the Real Thing.

episodes.description: Julian decides to depart Sunnyvale Trailer Park and go to community college to finally do something productive in his life.

episodes.description: Ricky and Bubbles agree to star in J-Roc's porno film but Ricky loses his nerve, forcing Bubbles to stand in for him on a particularly steamy scene.

episodes.description: Ricky lets a dog devour a tray of hash brownies and takes the dog to the local veterinarian. He must then run errands for the vet to pay for it.

episodes.description: Julian convinces Ricky that it's time to marry Lucy. Reluctant at first, Ricky changes his mind when Julian suggests that people will assume he's gay.

episodes.description: Lucy asks Julian to plan the wedding since she thinks Ricky is not up to it, but his plans ruin the wedding when the cops show up.

episodes.description: Julian and Ricky have to make sure that Jim Lahey wins the election for trailer park supervisor over their archrival Sam Losco, who is also running.

episodes.description: Needing extra cash to expand their dope operation without raising Lahey's suspicions, Julian and Ricky open a disco bar in J-Roc's trailer.

episodes.title: A Dope Trailer Is No Place for a Kitty
episodes.description: When their dope plants become infested with insects, Ricky and Julian quarantine the surviving crop in Bubbles's shed, leading to a fiery conclusion.

episodes.title: The Bible Pimp
episodes.description: A couple pretending to be a preacher and his daughter selling Bibles comes to the park, hoping to make off with lots of cash.

episodes.title: Never Trust a Man with No Shirt On
episodes.description: Randy joins Julian and Ricky in their life of crime. However, when Randy is caught spying on them, it puts their dope operation in danger.

episodes.description: Julian asks J-Roc to make another porno film to make Barb dump Sam, Ricky gets his Grade 10, and Julian successfully sells the hash.

episodes.description: After their release from prison, Ricky and Julian are free and rich, thanks to their huge dope sale to the prison guards and inmates.

episodes.description: Julian reveals a new plan to the boys that involves committing various small crimes so they can't go to jail, and saving the money for a cruise trip.

episodes.description: When Ricky plans to have a community day in the park complete with wrestling, Bubbles assumes the identity of a wrestler from "parts unknown."

episodes.description: When Bubbles has a toothache, he tries everything to get rid of it. Julian tells him that he must go to the hospital.

episodes.description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles find a mountain lion in their marijuana field eating their weed. Things get complicated when Bubbles befriends the animal.

episodes.description: The boys plan to smuggle the dope and sell it at a Snoop Dogg concert. Lahey asks Barb to marry him again, but Barb declines.

episodes.title: Working Man
episodes.description: The boys hold Rita MacNeil and her entourage hostage and force them to help harvest the dope crop. A hostile standoff ensues.

episodes.title: Give Peace a Chance
episodes.description: After a brief stint in jail, Ricky, Julian and Bubbles return to the trailer park in style, but soon discover that Trevor and Cory lost their money.

episodes.title: The Sh*t Puppets
episodes.description: Cory and Trevor go to work for Julian and help him steal hash from Cyrus, Terry and Dennis, then concoct a plan to hide it until they find a buyer.

episodes.title: The F**kin Way She Goes
episodes.description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles hide their hash under Ray's driveway. Ray's addictions worsen. Ricky barbecues for his family, with devastating results.

episodes.title: You Got to Blame the Thing Up Here
episodes.description: Ricky, Julian and Bubbles help Ray find a new home after his trailer burns down in a fire that Ricky caused. However, it's Bubbles who gets the blame.

episodes.description: Bubbles pretends to be a spaceman when the boys steal a rocket set. Ray reveals Lahey's secret, and Lahey goes off the deep end.

episodes.title: Don't Cross the Sh*t Line
episodes.description: Ray and Bubbles star in another of J-Roc's adult films, but Lahey and Randy confiscate J-Roc's tape, which has evidence of Ray's disability fraud.

episodes.title: The Winds of Sh*t
episodes.description: Ricky tries to go back to school but ends up working as a janitor selling dope to the students. Lahey has disturbing visions of the future.

episodes.title: I Am the Liquor
episodes.description: Ricky bails Trinity out of jail. Lahey goes on a bender and tricks Cory and Trevor into giving him information. Julian tries to get his trailer back.

episodes.title: Sh*t Blizzard
episodes.description: Cyrus and his gang are bailed out of jail by Randy and immediately go after Ricky, Julian and Bubbles for getting them busted and taking their hash.

episodes.description: This episode revolves around the conclusion of the boys' plan to smuggle dope to the United States. As usual, the plan doesn't go quite to plan.
